title: Dyer's Record Book (USA), 1880
inscribed: Label on cover reads:  "PRINT BOOK, SEPT. 15 / 80".
creditline: Gift of Frederick J. Whitehead from the collection compiled by his father Cornelius Whitehead at the Pacific Print Works of Lawrence, Massachusetts
description: A notebook with formulas for dyes to be used for printing textiles. Book contains 138 samples, mostly floral designs in brilliant colors. Front cover reads Print Book, Sept. 15, '80. Last part of book not used.

tombstone.epitaph: Dyer's Record Book (USA), 1880; Company: Old Pacific Print Works ; cardboard, paper, printed textile samples; H x W: 21 x 33.2 cm (8 1/4 x 13 1/16 in.); Gift of Frederick J. Whitehead from the collection compiled by his father Cornelius Whitehead at the Pacific Print Works of Lawrence, Massachusetts; 1945-55-9
